  "description": "The Global Satellite Mapping of precipitation (GSMAP) is developed by JAXA. The product takes advantages of the Global precipitation Measurement (GPM) mission constellation satellites to provide hourly rain rates. The rainfall estimation is based on the merging of microwave and infrared retrievals through LEO and GEO platforms. The product covers 60S to 60N globally.",
